{{Infobox company | name = 5Rocks | industry = Mobile analytics, game operation | logo = 5rocks_logo.png | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 2010 | founder = Changsu Lee | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = | location_country = | locations = [[Seoul]], [[Tokyo]] | area_served = | key_people = {{unordered list|'''Changsu Lee''': CEO |'''Chester Roh''': CSO }} | products = 5Rocks | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|5rocks.io/en}} | footnotes = | intl = | bodystyle = }} '''5Rocks''' is a company established in South Korea that specializes in providing [[business intelligence]] for [[lifetime value]] maximization for mobile game developers, publishers and [[ad network]] service providers. Its analytics tool offers not only analysis but also operation tool for mobile game clients.<ref name="ultralab">{{cite web | url = http://ultralab.co/5rocks-and-the-growing-demand-for-actionable-analytics/ | title = 5rocks and the growing demand for actionable analytics | publisher =UltraLab | author = Abel Acuña| accessdate = 26 May 2014}}</ref> Based on its unique cohort analytics and combined operation, mobile game operator or developer are enabled to communicate with their game users. 5Rocks provides push notification and in-app-campaign such as announcement, in-app product promotion, rewards, and cross promotion.<ref name="ultralab"/> In Apr 2014, the company announced that it had secured more than 400 clients over the world.<ref name="thekoreabizwire">{{cite web | url = http://koreabizwire.com/market-for-mobile-data-analytics-grows-fast-on-the-back-of-thriving-game-industry/10284| title = Market for Mobile Data Analytics Grows Fast on the Back of Thriving Game Industry | publisher =TheKoreaBizwire | author = Sean Chung| accessdate = 26 May 2014}}</ref> 5Rocks is funded by [[KDDI]], [[Adways]], [[Stonebridge Capital]] and recently Global Brain.<ref name="techinasia">{{cite web | url = http://www.techinasia.com/5rock-backed-strong-team-hopes-rock-game-analytics-world/| title =5Rocks, backed by a strong team, hopes to rock the game analytics world | publisher =TechInAsia | author = Yuna Kim | accessdate = 26 May 2014}}</ref> Mobile monetization and ad-tech firm Tapjoy acquired 5Rocks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://venturebeat.com/2014/08/06/driving-mobile-consolidation-tapjoy-acquires-5rocks-analytics-and-marketing-automation-firm/|title=Driving mobile consolidation, Tapjoy acquires 5Rocks analytics and marketing automation firm|date=2014-08-06|work=VentureBeat|access-date=2018-06-27|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/tapjoy-acquires-5rocks-korean-startup|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-27}}</ref>
