[[File:SR30 pyranometer.jpg|thumb|Typical ISO 9060 secondary standard pyranometer, model SR30.]]
'''ISO 9060''', ''Specification and classification of instruments for measuring hemispherical solar and direct solar radiation'', is an [[International Organization for Standardization|ISO]] standard for the classification of [[Pyranometer|pyranometers]] and [[Pyrheliometer|pyrheliometers]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iso.org/obp/ui/#iso:std:iso:9060:ed-1:v1:en|title=ISO 9060:1990 Solar energy — Specification and classification of instruments for measuring hemispherical solar and direct solar radiation |website=www.iso.org|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref>
