{{news release|1=article|date=October 2018}}
'''Modern Meadow''' is a company that produces Zoa, a biologically-produced,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2017/09/modern-meadow-lab-grown-leather/540285/|title=Leather, Grown in a Lab Without Cows|last=Zhang|first=Sarah|date=2017-09-21|work=The Atlantic|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> ethical and environmentally-friendly leather alternative<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chemengonline.com/protein-engineering-yields-animal-free-leather/|title=Protein engineering yields animal-free leather - Chemical Engineering {{!}} Page 1|website=www.chemengonline.com|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> that is based on bovine collagen.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/style/article/The-next-generation-of-clothing-is-coming-It-s-12848316.php|title=The next generation of clothing is coming. It's made by microbes.|date=2018-04-19|work=San Francisco Chronicle|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> The company was recognized by the [[World Economic Forum]] as a 2018 Technology Pioneer,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leathermag.com/features/featurematerial-gains-6713680/|title=Modern Meadow's first bioleather – Zoa - Leather International|website=''leathermag.com''|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> and a Zoa shirt is on permanent display at the [[Museum of Modern Art|MOMA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moma.org/artists/69271|title=Zoa {{!}} MoMA|website=www.moma.org|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> Modern Meadows was started in 2011<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/features/this-lab-grown-leather-could-hit-retailers-next-year|title=This lab-grown leather could hit retailers next year|last=Scipioni|first=Jade|date=2018-03-19|work=Fox Business|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> by CEO Andras Forgacs, formerly of [[Organovo]], a company that uses [[3D printing|3-D printing]] of human tissue for medical use.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.inc.com/magazine/201804/alden-wicker/prototype-modern-meadow-lab-grown-leather.html|title=The Future of Leather Is Growing in a New Jersey Lab--No Animals Needed|date=2018-03-13|work=''Inc.com''|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> Modern Meadow has raised approximately $54 million from investors including Singapore's Temasek and [[Horizons Ventures|Horizon Ventures]], the private investment fund of the Hong Kong billionaire, [[Li Ka-shing]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/10/04/business/modern-meadow/index.html|title=Would you wear leather that's grown in a lab?|last=Business|first=Andrea Lo, CNN|publisher=CNN|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> In 2018, Modern Meadow signed an agreement with [[Evonik Industries|Evonik]], a chemical company that specializes in microbial fermentation with the goal of commercially producing biofabricated leather.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/fashion-labels-look-to-be-cool-by-being-less-cruel-1532005200|title=Fashion Labels Scramble to Shed Their Skins|last=Dalton|first=Matthew|date=2018-07-19|work=The Wall Street Journal|access-date=2018-10-29|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> It takes two weeks to create Zoa in a lab, and the material can be made to match any thickness, texture<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1088930/no-animals-were-involved-in-producing-this-premium-leather/|title=Modern Meadow spent millions developing lab-grown leather — Quartz|website=Quartz|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> or color.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/03/09/modern-meadow-and-evonik-are-brewing-leather-in-a-lab.html|title=This leather is made in a lab, not from livestock|last=Kolodny|first=Lora|date=2018-03-09|publisher=CNBC|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref> Zoa can also be created in liquid form.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/cool-tech/modern-meadow-leather-here/|title=Modern Meadow’s Animal-Free Leather Is Finally Here, And It’s Awesome {{!}} Digital Trends|date=2017-10-02|work=Digital Trends|access-date=2018-10-29}}</ref>

